{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"chief-contained-hoopoe","description":"Activity-based liveness for agentic runs: a generous per-request read timeout + step caps + an idle-watchdog that resets on each stream event — and NO total-runtime timeout.\n\n## Why\nA single hard total-runtime timeout truncates healthy multi-minute / large-context (1M-token) runs. Liveness must be gauged by time-since-last-event, the proven pattern in the two most relevant mature runtimes: LangGraph `TimeoutPolicy.idle_timeout` and the Claude Agent SDK `CLAUDE_ASYNC_AGENT_STALL_TIMEOUT_MS` (both reset on stream events). pydantic-ai ships no total-run timeout (feature request closed not-planned), but exposes the event stream to build one.\n\n## What\n- Single-turn / structured calls: a generous but finite per-request read timeout (`httpx.Timeout(read=...)`, sized above worst-case large-context prefill) + `request_limit=2`.\n- Agentic calls: per-request read timeout + step caps (`request_limit`, `tool_calls_limit`) + an idle-watchdog via `event_stream_handler` that resets a last-event timestamp on every model-request / tool-call / token-delta event and aborts only after `idle_window` of TOTAL silence. No total-runtime timeout.\n- Tuning invariant: both the `read` timeout and `idle_window` must be >= worst-case time-to-first-token (a 1M-token prefill can be minutes of silence). Wrap the event iterator to avoid pydantic-ai #4796 (a failing tool + `event_stream_handler` raises an `AssertionError` that masks the real error).\n\n## Scope\n- Per-execution_mode timeout wiring; the watchdog task + cancellation handling; config keys `verify.llm_request_timeout_s`, `verify.llm_agentic_idle_timeout_s`.\n- NOT in scope: any total-runtime cap (explicitly rejected — it truncates healthy runs).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A generous per-request read timeout is set for both modes, sized for large-context prefill, and configurable.\n- [ ] Agentic runs get step caps + an idle-watchdog resetting on stream events; a run whose last event was < idle_window ago is never aborted (test with a slow-but-live injected model).\n- [ ] A stalled/zombie run (no events for > idle_window) is aborted and classified.\n- [ ] No total-runtime timeout exists anywhere in the gate path (asserted).\n- [ ] The #4796 event-iterator wrap is in place; `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`, `src/rebar/config.py`, `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`.","id":"fd1d-5f0d-4bd8-40f4","parent_id":"jira-reb-687","priority":2,"tags":["llm-resilience"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Activity-based liveness: per-request timeout + step caps + idle-watchdog (no total-runtime timeout)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783557853981684001,"uuid":"4c9d2b2f-099a-49ea-a2f4-df5f6c64a371"}